task.summary: - Modified IntelliJ project properties to add needed dependencies
- Changed some file paths in EnglishTwitterFilter to reflect paths on current machine
- Made some changes to the code in EnglishTwitterFilter to accommodate new file format and ensure that tweets are filtered properly

EnglishTwitterFilter: Changed code so that it creates one large data file with all the training data after filtering, rather than create files for each hashtag. TextUtility: Added some additional filtering methods - if a tweet has hashtags that contradict the file that it's from, those tweets are ignored. Tweets that are replies to other tweets (or quote other tweets) are also ignored. - Moved some members and methods around in both classes.

- Converted languageDetector to instance variable. - Added method to TextUtility to check whether a tweet is truncated or not (indicated by the presence of special ellipsis character at the end of the tweet) - Added method to EnglishTwitterFilter to create a balanced dataset from the filtered tweets - Updated workspace.xml

- Moved language detection to separate function because every object of the language detector class (Detector) can only detect the language for a single piece of text (returns the same language code for subsequent tweets, even if they are in a different language, if the append() method is called over and over.)
- Fixed a syntax error and commented out a debug statement
- Changed language detection code and changed output directory for filtered data
Added properties file and changed input/output paths to use properties from the file
Moved properties file to its own package
Added command-line args to EnglishTwitterFilter to specify the week range to be filtered.
